THE FACTS KHUMBULANI Sotaka from Katlehong, east of Joburg, said he was beaten by his boss in June last year. He said he also insulted him and called him names in front of his colleagues. Khumbulani said he tried many times to get help without success. ADVICE Abuse and harassment is a violation of human rights and dignity. The employee can report the case to the relevant union and the case must be investigated and disciplinary action taken against the person. Alternatively, the employee can open an assault case against his boss.